[[File:Ambient Sound Investments - Ahti Heinla.jpg|thumb|Ahti Heinla in 2007.]]
'''Ahti Heinla''' (born 2 May 1972) is an [[Estonia]]n [[programmer]] and [[entrepreneur]]. He is one of the developers of [[Skype]].

He was also an organizer of [[Let's Do It 2008]], a civic action with 50,000 volunteers participating in cleaning up the countryside of Estonia in one day.

He was a recipient of the 2008 [[Estonian Volunteer of the Year]] national award.

He has been a member of the board at the nature protection [[Non-governmental organization|NGO]] [[Estonian Fund for Nature]] since 2006.

Heinla speaks [[Estonian language|Estonian]], [[English language|English]] and [[Spanish language|Spanish]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.linkedin.com/in/ahtiheinla/|title=Ahti Heinla's LinkedIn profile|accessdate=October 8, 2017}}</ref>

In 2013 and 2014 he participated on [[Centennial Challenges|NASA Centennial Challenge]] as team leader for [[Team Kuukulgur]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nasa.gov/sites/default/files/teambiosinteractivemap-final.pdf#page7| title=SRR14 Team Bios for Map| accessdate=July 7, 2017| date=June 4, 2014| publisher=[[NASA]]}}</ref>

Heinla and [[Janus Friis]] founded [[Starship Technologies]] in 2014, to develop small self-driving delivery robots. He serves as CEO and CTO in it.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.starship.xyz/ahti-heinla/| title=Ahti Heinla, co-founder, CEO and CTO|accessdate=July 7, 2017}}</ref>

